content:
OmniScript Action Elements

Make a Data Mapper outbound call to populate an OmniScript with data from SFDC objects. Inputs Data Mapper Interface name and input parameters.

Data Mapper Extract Action

Commit data from OmniScript to SFDC objects. Inputs Data Mapper Interface name, Data JSON of OmniScript, and filesMap.

Data Mapper Post Action

Send the full OmniScript Data JSON to Data Mapper and returns the mapping from the Data Mapper.

OmniScript Data Mapper Transform Action

Delete specified records from an sObject. Objects are specified by ID.

If the JSON contains a list of accounts like this:

  {
    "Account": [
      {
        "accId": ["001f400000EPQ8o", "001f400000BAkbn"]
      }
    ]
  }	

You can delete it by specifying the following merge field in the Path to Id field: %Account:accId%

To specify messages to be displayed to users when the operation succeeds or fails, set the corresponding fields in the Error Messages section.

Decision Matrix	Call a decision matrix with specified inputs and return the result to an OmniScript.	

Call a Decision Matrix from an OmniScript

Send an email that contains the prefilled documents for signing or reviewing. It can be sent to one or more recipients.

Using the DocuSign Envelope Action to Email Documents for Signature

Display a modal containing a DocuSign document. The OmniScript user can sign the document directly from the modal and download a PDF of the signed document.

Using the DocuSign Signature Action to Sign Documents From Within an OmniScript

Use the Salesforce Email API to send an email template to the email address of a User, Lead, or Contact or to send an email body defined in the action configuration to any email address.

HTTP Action

Call an internal and external web service from OmniScript without coding or making Salesforce API calls using the HTTP Action.

Invoke an Integration Procedure to retrieve Salesforce data and external data.

Navigate to various Salesforce experiences from OmniScript using the Navigate Action element.

Call Apex classes from OmniScript using the Remote Action element.

Handle OmniScript end-user errors.

Set Errors In an OmniScript

Handle values of elements on a hidden node, a current step, or a future step.

Set Values in an OmniScript
title: OmniScript Action Elements and Data Mappers
